---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 16, 2025';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Brewio"
  description="Terms and conditions for using the Brewio mobile application."
>
  <Nav />

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <div class="page-eyebrow">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="page-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <main class="content">
    <div class="content-inner">

      <p class="lead">
        Please read these Terms of Service carefully before using the Brewio mobile
        application. By creating an account or using the app, you agree to be bound
        by these terms.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By downloading, installing, or using Brewio ("the App"), you agree to these
          Terms of Service and our Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not
          use the App.
        </p>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to update these terms at any time. Continued use of the
          App after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p>
          Brewio is a mobile application for coffee enthusiasts. The App allows users to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Log and track coffee brews with detailed parameters and ratings</li>
          <li>Follow step-by-step brewing guides and timers for 12+ methods</li>
          <li>Manage a coffee bean stash with freshness tracking</li>
          <li>Calculate dose, water ratio, and extraction yield</li>
          <li>Discover specialty coffee roasters worldwide</li>
          <li>Track brewing streaks and earn achievement badges</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Some features require a Brewio Premium subscription. Features available under
          each tier are described within the App and may change over time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. User Accounts</h2>
        <p>
          To use Brewio, you must create an account using Apple Sign In or Google Sign In.
          You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account and for
          all activity that occurs under it.
        </p>
        <p>
          You must provide accurate information and keep it up to date. You must be at
          least 13 years old to use the App.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Subscriptions & Payments</h2>
        <p>
          Brewio offers a free tier and an optional Brewio Premium subscription.
          Subscriptions are managed through the Apple App Store or Google Play Store and
          are subject to their respective terms.
        </p>

        <h3>Billing</h3>
        <p>
          Subscription fees are billed in advance on a monthly or annual basis, depending
          on the plan you select. Payment is charged to your App Store or Google Play
          account upon confirmation of purchase.
        </p>

        <h3>Cancellation</h3>
        <p>
          You may cancel your subscription at any time through your App Store or Google
          Play account settings. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current
          billing period. We do not provide refunds for partial subscription periods.
        </p>

        <h3>Free Trial</h3>
        <p>
          Where offered, free trials convert to a paid subscription automatically at the
          end of the trial period unless cancelled beforehand.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. User Content</h2>
        <p>
          You retain ownership of all content you create in the App (brew logs, notes,
          recipes). By using the App, you grant us a limited licence to store and process
          this content solely to provide the service to you.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are responsible for ensuring your content does not violate any applicable
          laws or third-party rights.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Prohibited Conduct</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the App for any unlawful purpose</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the App or its infrastructure</li>
          <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or disassemble the App</li>
          <li>Use automated tools to scrape or collect data from the App</li>
          <li>Impersonate any person or entity</li>
          <li>Interfere with or disrupt the integrity or performance of the App</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The App, including its design, code, text, graphics, and branding, is owned by
          Brewio and protected by applicable intellectual property laws. Nothing in these
          terms grants you any right to use our trademarks, logos, or brand features
          without our prior written consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The App is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind,
          either express or implied. We do not warrant that the App will be uninterrupted,
          error-free, or free of harmful components.
        </p>
        <p>
          Brewing guides and calculators in the App are provided for informational
          purposes only. Results may vary based on equipment, ingredients, and technique.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, Brewio shall not be liable for any
          indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from
          your use of, or inability to use, the App — even if we have been advised of
          the possibility of such damages.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our total liability to you for any claims arising from these terms or your use
          of the App shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding
          the claim.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your account at our discretion if
          you violate these terms or engage in conduct we determine to be harmful to other
          users or the App.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may delete your account at any time through the App settings. Upon
          termination, your right to use the App ceases immediately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with applicable
          law. Any disputes arising under these terms shall be subject to the exclusive
          jurisdiction of the competent courts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="contact-block">
          <p><strong>Brewio</strong></p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@brewio.app">hello@brewio.app</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://brewio.app">brewio.app</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── Page header ── */
  .page-header {
    background: var(--dark);
    padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dark);
  }

  .page-header-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    color: var(--cream);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(250,247,242,0.4);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  /* ── Content ── */
  .content {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 5rem 2rem 7rem;
  }

  .content-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.875rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--amber);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  a:hover { color: var(--amber-light); }

  /* Contact block */
  .contact-block {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .contact-block p { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .contact-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
</style>
